# Security Considerations

## Authentication & Authorization

### User Authentication
- Implement secure password storage using bcrypt or Argon2 with appropriate salt rounds
- Enforce strong password policies (minimum length, complexity requirements)
- Store session tokens securely and implement proper session management
- Consider implementing JWT with appropriate expiration times

### Authorization
- Implement proper access control for chat rooms and group chats
- Ensure users can only access chats they are authorized to view
- Implement proper role-based access control for group chat owners
- Validate all user inputs and permissions on both client and server side

## Data Security

### Message Security
- Implement end-to-end encryption for chat messages
- Use secure WebSocket connections (WSS) for real-time communication
- Ensure message persistence with proper encryption at rest

### Media Security
- Implement proper file type validation
- Use secure URLs for media access with appropriate expiration
- Implement proper access control for media files

## Infrastructure Security

### Network Security
- Use HTTPS for all web traffic
- Implement proper CORS policies
- Use secure WebSocket connections
- Implement rate limiting for API endpoints
- Use proper firewall rules and security groups

### Database Security
- Implement proper database access controls
- Use parameterized queries to prevent SQL injection

### Cloud Security
- Use secure cloud storage for media files
- Implement proper IAM roles and permissions
- Use secure secrets management
- Use secure container configurations

## Application Security

### Input Validation
- Implement proper input validation for all user inputs
- Use parameterized queries for database operations
- Implement proper output encoding
- Validate file uploads
- Implement proper error handling

### API Security
- Implement proper API authentication
- Use rate limiting for API endpoints
- Implement proper API versioning
- Use secure API endpoints
- Implement proper API documentation

## Monitoring and Logging

